Activity: A11 - Discover 5 unique access control devices

Objective
The goal of this activity was to investigate different types of access control devices used to restrict and manage access to systems, buildings, and sensitive areas

Method
I observed and researched various access control devices used in everyday environments such as schools, workplaces, and public areas. I dentified how each device controls access and what type of authentication it uses

Findings
The following access control devices were identified:
1. Key card access system - uses RFID cards to grant entry to building or restricted areas
2. Biometric fingerprint scanner - uses fingerprint recognition to authenticate users
3. Facial recognition system - uses cameras and facial data to verify identity
4. Smartphone based access - allows users to unlock doors using mobile apps or digital keys

Security Principle
The devices support authentication and access control, ensuring that only authorised individuals can enter restricted areas. they also contribute to confidentiality by preventing unauthorised access to sensitive locations or systems

